# Authoritative ground-truth record for this template. The registry generator
# (build_registry.py) copies the block below verbatim into eval/templates/README.md;
# --verify re-runs the query against GraphDB and asserts the live answer still
# equals the `answer` set. Keep it in sync with the query (or let --verify catch you).
#
# --- registry ---
# seed: CDH1
# seed_uri: ncbigene:999
# chain: reference-entity label lookup (fuzzy/semantic — no traversal derives this answer)
# answer:
#   - CDH1
# --- end registry ---
#
# Type 10_fuzzy_semantic. This query is a LABEL LOOKUP, not an answer derivation: it
# pins the canonical label of the hand-chosen reference entity (CDH1, the E-cadherin
# gene) so the reference is graph-anchored and --verify-able, NOT a traversal that
# answers "which gene's loss promotes metastasis" — no such edge exists, which is the
# point of this type (H4). The system under test never sees this query; it answers
# the natural-language question, and an LLM judge scores semantic equivalence to CDH1
# (accepting synonyms like "E-cadherin"). Seed reuses the README early observation:
# vector retrieval surfaced CDH1 by the metastasis/cell-adhesion language of its
# abstracts, while the graph could only reach it via an explicit gene-disease edge.

PREFIX hetio: <https://het.io/schema/>
PREFIX ncbigene: <https://identifiers.org/ncbigene/>
PREFIX rdfs: <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#>

SELECT ?gene ?geneLabel WHERE {
  VALUES ?gene { ncbigene:999 }       # CDH1 (E-cadherin) — reference entity, hand-chosen
  ?gene a hetio:Gene ;
        rdfs:label ?geneLabel .
}
